    "pattern": "Hash map + doubly linked list LRU",
    "visual": "Map key->node; the list keeps MRU at the front, LRU at the tail",
    "memorize": "get/put -> remove+insertFront; over capacity -> evict tail.prev",
    "scene": "A cursed closet: touching an item teleports it to the front; when full, the moldy back shoe gets yeeted into the void — get/put -> remove+insertFront; evict tail.prev.",
    "acquired": "Haunted doubly-linked closet: touch teleports to head; overflow yeets tail.prev—map pins each soul to its node",
    "time": "O(1) get/put",
    "space": "O(capacity)",
    "code": "package main\ntype node struct {\n\tkey, val   int\n\tprev, next *node\n}\n\ntype LRUCache struct {\n\tcap        int\n\tcache      map[int]*node\n\thead, tail *node\n}\n\nfunc Constructor(capacity int) LRUCache {\n\th, t := &node{}, &node{}\n\th.next, t.prev = t, h\n\treturn LRUCache{cap: capacity, cache: map[int]*node{}, head: h, tail: t}\n}\n\nfunc (c *LRUCache) remove(n *node) { n.prev.next, n.next.prev = n.next, n.prev }\nfunc (c *LRUCache) addHead(n *node) {\n\tn.next, n.prev = c.head.next, c.head\n\tc.head.next.prev, c.head.next = n, n\n}\nfunc (c *LRUCache) moveHead(n *node) { c.remove(n); c.addHead(n) }\n\nfunc (c *LRUCache) Get(key int) int {\n\tif n, ok := c.cache[key]; ok {\n\t\tc.moveHead(n)\n\t\treturn n.val\n\t}\n\treturn -1\n}\n\nfunc (c *LRUCache) Put(key, value int) {\n\tif n, ok := c.cache[key]; ok {\n\t\tn.val = value\n\t\tc.moveHead(n)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif len(c.cache) >= c.cap {\n\t\tlru := c.tail.prev\n\t\tc.remove(lru)\n\t\tdelete(c.cache, lru.key)\n\t}\n\tn := &node{key: key, val: value}\n\tc.cache[key] = n\n\tc.addHead(n)\n}\n",
